Class Summary
Column<T> Represents a distinct data type within a record.
IntegerColumn Represents a Column of type Integer sized to 4 bytes.
LongColumn Represents a Column of type Long sized to 8 bytes.
NamespaceRecordFile NamespaceRecordFile defines a record file that contains namespace records.
NamespaceRecordFile.NamespaceEntry NamespaceRecordFile.NamespaceEntry encapsulates the data held in columns defined by the namespace record.
NamespaceRecordFile.NamespaceRecord NamespaceRecordFile.NamespaceRecord defines a record that understands how to read and write namespace data represented as bytes or the encapsulated namespace entry.
Record<T> Models a record for some <T> contained by a RecordFile.
RecordFile Record files are a representation of files that contain fixed-length records.
StringColumn Represents a Column of type String where the length of the string is arbitrary.
 

Enum Summary
RecordMode Enumerated representation of record mode.
